  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Geneva Study Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cverse2",
        "text": "{e} And how hear we every man in our own tongue, wherein we were born?",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "cverse3",
            "text": "{e}",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " And how hear we every man in our own tongue, wherein we were born?",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(e) Not that they spoke one language, and different languages were heard, but the apostles spoke with different languages: for otherwise the miracle would have been in the hearers, whereas it is really in the speakers; Nazianzen in his oration of Whitsunday.",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
